Bootstrap Grid: https://www.sitepoint.com/bootstrap-grid-mastering-flexbox/
 
Try it Yourself
Let's build this mini project in the VS Code IDE. Don't forget to join the AlmaBetter Community to share your brilliant approaches and cheer each other on! 🚀 Happy coding! 💻😄
Task 1: Bootstrap lovers, this one's for you! Take up this challenge and show off your understanding of Bootstrap in the VS Code IDE.
Problem
Task: Customizing the Card Layout
Card Design:
Customize the background color and text color of the cards:
Set the background color to a light gray (#f8f9fa).
Set the text color to a dark gray (#333).
Add a box-shadow to the cards to give them a subtle depth effect.
Adjust the padding and margins to provide appropriate spacing between cards.
Image Styling:
Add a border-radius to the card images to give them rounded corners.
Set the height of the images to 250px to maintain a consistent size.
Button Styling:
Customize the button style:
Change the background color to a shade of blue (#007bff).
Set the text color to white (#fff).
Increase the font size and adjust the padding to make the button more prominent.
Add a hover effect to the button to make it interactive.
Responsive Design:
Ensure that the card layout is responsive and adapts to different screen sizes.
Test the responsiveness by resizing the browser window or using device emulators.
Optional:
Add any additional customizations or enhancements to further improve the visual appearance or user experience of the card layout. This could include animations, transitions, or other creative elements.
Solution
